values.description:
An Intel Real Sense R200 camera model.

* Composed by two grayscale-camera sensors (imitating infrared), one color-camera sensor and one depth-camera sensor.
* The RealSensePlugin, when associated to this model, publishes the 4 main streams of the RealSense camera (ir1, ir2, color and depth) in the same format as the real camera.

RealSense plugin pull request: [gazebo:2366](https://bitbucket.org/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/2366)

This is an updated version with a longer platform.

* The masses have been updated (using aluminum as material).
* The inertia has been approximated to the inertia of the base.
* Added start and finish lines.
* The doorway is now composed by two nested models: the static `src_doorframe` and `src_door`.

values.description:
https://acroname.com/products/r367-sf30-b?sku=R367-SF30-B
The LightWare SF30/B is a high speed, light weight laser rangefinder for mapping and obstacle detection by robotic vehicles such as UAVs with a range up to 50m.  It weighs 35g. More information can be found on the site I put up above. It's a single beam which has an update rate of around 18k.

Can be used as a sensor along with hector_quadrotor or similar.
values.title: Added a Lightware sf30 LRF sensor
